docs.abstract: Senator Jeff Merkley asked the F.B.I. to open an inquiry, citing a document that he said conflicted with the homeland security secretary’s congressional testimony on family separations at the border.
docs.snippet: Senator Jeff Merkley asked the F.B.I. to open an inquiry, citing a document that he said conflicted with the homeland security secretary’s congressional testimony on family separations at the border.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — A Democratic senator asked the F.B.I. on Friday to open a perjury investigation into the homeland security secretary, Kirstjen Nielsen, over her congressional testimony about the Trump administration’s policy of separating migrant families at the southern border.

headline.main: Democratic Senator Seeks Perjury Investigation of Kirstjen Nielsen

docs.abstract: Many members of the military now include yoga — often taught by veterans — as an element of their workout routine, and veterans turn to the practice for therapeutic applications.
docs.snippet: Many members of the military now include yoga — often taught by veterans — as an element of their workout routine, and veterans turn to the practice for therapeutic applications.
docs.lead_paragraph: To casual observers of either military service or the practice of yoga, the path from Oorah to Om may not seem obvious. But the intersection of yogi and veteran is natural if unexpected, beginning with the five classic yoga poses known as warriors.

headline.main: Yoga and Veterans: A Different Kind of Warrior
headline.print_headline: When ‘Your Commanding Officer Is Your Breath’

docs.abstract: The Senate will take up President Trump’s offer to pair wall funding with some immigrant legal protections, but an added measure to restrict asylum claims has drawn protests.
docs.snippet: The Senate will take up President Trump’s offer to pair wall funding with some immigrant legal protections, but an added measure to restrict asylum claims has drawn protests.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The Senate is poised as early as Tuesday to act on a Trump-backed measure to end the partial government shutdown, but a bill promoted as a compromise to pair the president’s wall with legal protections for some immigrants would also severely restrict migrants’ ability to claim asylum, drawing fierce opposition from immigrant rights groups.

headline.main: G.O.P. Bill to End Shutdown Draws Protests Over Asylum Restrictions

byline.original: By Sheryl Gay Stolberg and Julie Hirschfeld Davis

docs.abstract: With competing votes planned for Thursday, the Senate will finally move off the sidelines a month into the partial government shutdown.
docs.snippet: With competing votes planned for Thursday, the Senate will finally move off the sidelines a month into the partial government shutdown.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The Senate will hold competing votes on Thursday on President Trump’s proposal to spend $5.7 billion on a border wall and on a Democratic bill that would fund the government through Feb. 8 without a wall. It will be the first time the Senate has stepped off the sidelines to try to end the monthlong government shutdown.

headline.main: Senate Leaders Plan Competing Bills to End Shutdown
headline.print_headline: Senate Will Hold Competing Votes To End Shutdown

docs.abstract: “BUILD A WALL & CRIME WILL FALL!” Mr. Trump tweeted. But a border wall would not suddenly alter the population of undocumented immigrants.
docs.snippet: “BUILD A WALL & CRIME WILL FALL!” Mr. Trump tweeted. But a border wall would not suddenly alter the population of undocumented immigrants.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — As new polls released on Wednesday showed that a majority of Americans had cooled to the idea of a protracted government shutdown over his long-promised border wall, President Trump woke up with the same two options facing him as the past 33 days: He could fight back or concede.

headline.main: Trump’s Latest Border Sell: A (Factually Dubious) Rhyme

docs.abstract: Two years ago, the court struck down a ban on disparaging trademarks. Now, in a case about a clothing line’s name, it will consider what to do about scandalous ones.
docs.snippet: Two years ago, the court struck down a ban on disparaging trademarks. Now, in a case about a clothing line’s name, it will consider what to do about scandalous ones.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The Supreme Court, which is pretty squeamish about vulgar language, recently agreed to hear a case about whether the owner of a line of clothing sold under the brand name FUCT can register a trademark for the term.

headline.main: Trademark Fight Over Vulgar Term’s ‘Phonetic Twin’ Heads to Supreme Court
headline.print_headline: Trademark Fight Over Vulgar Term’s ‘Phonetic Twin’ Is Heading to Supreme Court

docs.abstract: The group representing the bureau’s special agents pressed for the government to reopen, citing limits on their ability to pursue crime and terrorism.
docs.snippet: The group representing the bureau’s special agents pressed for the government to reopen, citing limits on their ability to pursue crime and terrorism.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — As the partial government shutdown enters its fifth week, the funding freeze has impeded F.B.I. efforts to crack down on child trafficking, violent crime and terrorism, according to a report issued Tuesday by the group that represents the bureau’s 13,000 special agents.

headline.main: Report Says Shutdown Is Impeding F.B.I.’s Law Enforcement Efforts
headline.print_headline: F.B.I. Agents’ Leader Says Resources Are ‘Stretched to the Breaking Point’

docs.abstract: Representative Sheila Jackson Lee will resign as chairwoman of the Congressional Black Caucus Foundation after a former aide said she was fired for pursuing a sexual assault case against a supervisor.
docs.snippet: Representative Sheila Jackson Lee will resign as chairwoman of the Congressional Black Caucus Foundation after a former aide said she was fired for pursuing a sexual assault case against a supervisor.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Representative Sheila Jackson Lee, facing fallout from a lawsuit that claims she fired an aide who said she was sexually assaulted by a supervisor at the Congressional Black Caucus Foundation, resigned on Wednesday as the foundation’s chairwoman.

headline.main: Sheila Jackson Lee Leaves 2 Posts After Aide Says She Was Fired for Reporting Sexual Assault
headline.print_headline: Texas Democrat Leaves Posts as Pressure Builds Over Firing of Ex-Aide

docs.lead_paragraph: A Texas judge denied the motion by the conspiracy theorist Alex Jones to dismiss a defamation lawsuit brought against him and his Infowars operation by the parents of a Sandy Hook shooting victim, in a ruling released on Thursday.

headline.main: Judge Rules Against Alex Jones and Infowars in Sandy Hook Lawsuit
headline.print_headline: Judge Rejects Bid to Dismiss One of the Infowars Lawsuits
